cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "research-atlas: a reconciled graph of the global research economy"
message: "If you use this software or data, please cite it as below."
type: software
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20774322
identifiers:
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.20774322
    description: Concept DOI (always resolves to the latest version)
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.20774323
    description: Version DOI (v0.1.0)
authors:
  - given-names: Gianangelo
    family-names: Dichio
    affiliation: Bucket Foundation
repository-code: "https://github.com/bucket-foundation/research-atlas"
url: "https://bucket.foundation"
abstract: >-
  research-atlas ingests global public research funding and output into one
  normalized, validated graph (Funder -> Grant -> Organization[ROR] ->
  Person[ORCID] -> Work[OpenAlex/DOI] -> Field) and publishes it as open,
  citable datasets, with a connector framework, a validation suite, and a
  reproducible metascience analysis pipeline.
keywords:
  - metascience
  - science of science
  - research funding
  - knowledge graph
  - OpenAlex
  - ROR
  - ORCID
